RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 1 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 77. Maiden Special Weight Purse 111600. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: POPNFIZZ hounded the early frontrunner while under a snug hold entering the turn, engaged for the lead outside two furlongs from the wire, took command between horses at the top of the stretch and had enough left in reserve to hold off the closing runner at the finish. ATTABE was allowed to settle near the back in the beginning, was roused angling outside at the quarter marker, began to find her best stride five wide in mid stretch and was full of run late gaining but could not get there in time. GAMBLE'S ORB tracked the early pacesetters three wide at the half, joined the battle up front outside the contesting leaders turning for home but did not switch leads until very late and could not find more in deep stretch. JANIS JOPLIN took a stalking position behind the early leaders into the turn, waited on the rail with five sixteenths to run, shifted out to the four path for the stretch drive but could only run evenly late for a minor share. NOT NEGOTIABLE broke sharp to set the pace down the backside, was headed outside midway on the turn, battled inside in upper stretch and faded on the fence the final sixteenth. NEOLITHIC NATION was unhurried settling inside at the back in the early stages, saved ground through the turn but could not be a presence in the stretch drive.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 2 5F All Weather Track CR: 93. Optional Claiming Purse 61800. RACE.FOOTNOTES: HIGHLY FLAMMABLE had a nice trip watching the front duo battle in the early stages, cruised three wide outside foes to assume command at the top of the lane and comfortably drew away when asked. FOREST BUZZ chased the early speed at the break, took over the top spot outside three furlongs from home, was collared by the winner in mid stretch, could no fight that one off but ran on well to be a clear second. BET N WIN took a stalking position in the two path near the rear in the beginning, was scrubbing on for more run with five sixteenths to go, offered little response and could not get involved for the stretch run. MIGHT BEE SPEEDY trailed the field outside down the backstretch, something appeared amiss entering the far turn and could not keep pace with the field, regrouped in upper stretch and had some late energy to close the gap on the field at the wire.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 3 5F All Weather Track CR: 93. Claiming Purse 51000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHANCEL kept a close eye on the early pacesetter racing outside down the backstretch, continued to hound the speed on the turn, began to wear down the leader under left handed urging in mid stretch to get up a few strides before the wire. LIGHT THE LAMP was away alertly to dictate the pace, continued to be the frontrunner on the turn, opened up mildly on the eventual winner turning for home but could not find enough late to hold that one off in the end. STERLING SPEED had a good inside position watching the leaders in the beginning parts of the race, was asked for more run but could not threaten the top two down the lane but fought on gamely when shifted just off the fence at the furlong marker to win the battle for the show prize. KID FORESTER tracked outside foes in the second flight entering the turn, put in a mild rally at the top of the stretch and stalled at the eighth pole losing the battle in the end for the show money. ONE PUNCH CHARLIE was in tight quarters running between rivals at the half mile marker and was shuffled back to near the rear, in upper stretch was roused for more effort and had little to give late while finishing on the fence. BIG WARDEN broke well with the field at the start, could not keep pace with runners early and trailed into the turn, raced three wide outside horses but could not make an impression running to the wire.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: STORMY SOUL contended between runners early then continued to duel inside a rival but off the fence into and on the turn, forged clear in the stretch under steady handling. BAHAMIAN DUDE attended the early pace from inside, was in a bit tight and tapped on the brakes outside the three-eighths, steadily dropped back.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: NAPA SPIRIT (IRE) pressed the early pace outside, took command seven sixteenths from home, was headed outside at the quarter marker and stubbornly ran on inside to draw away from challenger in the last sixteenth. RACE.FOOTNOTES: READY FOR A FIGHT bumped lightly with a rival after the break, tracked from between runners in the second flight going two to three wide on the turn, angled out five deep at the top of the stretch, took aim and drove past inside the final sixteenth. RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 8 5F All Weather Track CR: 82. Claiming Purse 40200. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. RACE.FOOTNOTES: EXCEED had a good tracking trip behind the contesting front duo, waited patiently to pounce on the turn, found clear running room in the three path at the top of the lane and wore down the leader in the late stages for the victory. PRINCE SUSSEX showed good speed to lead on the rail at the half, continued to set the fractions on the turn, stubbornly gave way racing on the wrong lead inside through the stretch and just missed at the finish in a gutsy effort. ORPHAN HALLIE made a good move for position from the outside post down the backstretch to enter the turn tracking outside runners in the second flight, rallied four wide into the stretch drive and closed well to get up for the show award. TWO YEAR CONTRACT was in tight behind and between runners at the half, regrouped between horses to rally five sixteenths from the line and showed good energy through the lane passing tired runners for a minor placing. BIG INVESTMENT rated on the rail midfield down the backstretch, was urged inside midpoint on the turn, spurted up the fence to be in with a chance for a share in upper stretch and levelled out for the final sixteenth. STYLISH GENT pressured the pace on the outside in the early stages, drifted outwards when they straightened out for the drive, could not find more run and retreated in mid stretch. ARTIE'S ALL IN raced three wide outside foes near the rear in the beginning, could not gain on fellow rivals racing on the turn, drifted out when roused entering the stretch and could not be a factor to the line.
